    QuakeMLConversion
    This class is the main for processing data from the database of e-mail messages from the cat2qml table to QuakeML.
    QuakeMLHelper
    This attempts to organize the various common bulletin elements into calls for each major element so logic that would be common to many bulletin translations can be put in one place Normal ordering : 1) Create a QuakeMLHelper generally through the format specific subclass, 2) addEventParameters() - make QML document for this event, adds author/creator infor 3) addEvent() - add an event to this QuakeML document (it might be a catalog of events) 4) addPicks() - like addGSEPick() 5) addMagnitude - add one or more magnitudes to the QuakeML 6) addOrigin - add one or more origins to the EventParameters 7) call writeEventXML() to create a file with the XML It includes many helper static methods for dealling with makeRealQuantity with various scales and uncertainties to cut down on the excessive decimal places that default realQuantities display with.
    SeisSan  
    XMLChecker
    This class tests the quakeML checking put into the USGS based Convertor.
